(* Beginning of Notebook Content *)
Notebook[{
Cell["Discrete Phase Space, Computed", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"ffe0b2ce-d675-4476-abda-bd7026235e68"],

Cell["\<\
Finite-dimensional quantum mechanics as a computational laboratory in Wolfram \
Language + QuantumFramework\
\>", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"947d15e3-9980-452b-9812-dd712d85e85b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A qubit, a qutrit, or any ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["d", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "eac164f8-9476-4302-8769-6b7833d978ca"],
 "-level system has a phase space just as surely as a particle on a line \
does, except that the plane ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "90751362-ba87-406f-81f0-09ce3c66bee5"],
 " is replaced by a finite ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["d", "TI"], "\[Times]", 
   StyleBox["d", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "afa699aa-9471-44ca-9fc7-2303cd4c0609"],
 " grid of points and the Wigner function becomes a finite table of real \
numbers, some of them negative. This document is a computation-first tour of \
that formalism. Every object we discuss, the phase-point operators, the \
discrete Wigner function, its negativity, the magic monotone mana, the \
symmetric informationally complete measurements, the mutually unbiased bases, \
the Weyl transform, and finally the dynamics, is built explicitly and \
evaluated, so it can be tested, modified, and extended. The conviction behind \
this style is simple: if we cannot compute it, we do not yet understand it."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b50fa74d-c394-41bb-ae09-4f70758e74b8"],

Cell["\<\
We start from the finite Heisenberg-Weyl group (the discrete cousins of \
position and momentum), build the phase-point operators from it, and use them \
to define the Wigner function. We then read three physical facts straight off \
that function: which states are \"classical\" (the discrete Hudson theorem), \
how much magic a state carries (mana), and why negativity is the same thing \
as contextuality. We change frames to the SIC and MIC measurements that \
underlie the QBist reconstruction of the Born rule, pass through mutually \
unbiased bases, invert the Wigner map with the Weyl transform, and close by \
evolving a state directly on the phase-space grid, as a flow generated by the \
Braasch-Wootters rate matrix, and checking it against ordinary Schr\
\[ODoubleDot]dinger evolution to machine precision. The point of the exercise \
is that a formalism usually presented on paper becomes something you run.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"925c6a8b-f8ac-42af-b8d1-6d549af2dc07"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A note on the environment. Load the paclet once; the phase-space transforms \
are an experimental part of the framework, so we load the working tree \
explicitly. Every cell below is meant to be evaluated in order, and you are \
encouraged to change the dimension ",
 Cell[BoxData["d"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "32b2095c-48af-4cd8-b8d8-73c0c716ff9f"],
 ", the state, or the Hamiltonian and watch the numbers move."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b33ac0a3-a742-40a1-a0f1-ee365808cde1"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
  "PacletDirectoryLoad", 
   "[", "\"\</Users/mohammadb/Documents/GitHub/QuantumFramework/\
QuantumFramework\>\"", "]"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<Wolfram`QuantumFramework`\>\"", "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[1]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"5938097d-8553-40d0-9297-daa9eb6bcef8"],

Cell["1. The finite Heisenberg-Weyl group", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"99299b3a-d288-414b-947a-604f6fbec7a7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Continuous phase space is generated by two operators, position and \
momentum, that fail to commute. The finite-dimensional analogue replaces them \
by two unitary operators on a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["d", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a854b2ba-0f8e-4101-9fa0-ddc685324789"],
 "-dimensional space: the ",
 StyleBox["shift",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["X", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3fb9e1ea-224b-4036-9bbc-2a5e1020f38c"],
 ", which advances the computational basis ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["n", "TI"]},
     "Ket"]}], "=", 
   TemplateBox[{
     RowBox[{
       StyleBox["n", "TI"], "+", "1", 
       StyleBox["mod", FontSlant -> "Plain"], 
       StyleBox["d", "TI"]}]},
    "Ket"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e770e281-7455-4125-92ef-73bd8024b53c"],
 ", and the ",
 StyleBox["clock",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4ae77008-2d98-4af2-bc38-2ef7ea4bc930"],
 ", which stamps each basis state with a phase ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["n", "TI"]},
     "Ket"]}], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["\[Omega]", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["n", "TI"]], 
    TemplateBox[{
      StyleBox["n", "TI"]},
     "Ket"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7ba7bfff-30c0-481b-bd1e-2a6ad0319a1a"],
 ", where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Omega]", "TI"], "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{"2", "\[Pi]", 
     StyleBox["i", "TI"], "/", 
     StyleBox["d", "TI"]}]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2488ffa5-78ef-4987-ae7f-8661766e784c"],
 ". Together they generate the Heisenberg-Weyl (generalized Pauli) group, and \
the single relation that defines the whole structure is the discrete Weyl \
commutation law ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], "=", 
   StyleBox["\[Omega]", "TI"], " ", 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7f4f2ae1-8389-4966-92b1-45190a5b8db5"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bbc4b98a-5bb6-4a64-a0ba-d15d57e3ff34"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Define the clock and shift in dimension ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["d", "TI"], "=", "3"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "41996e28-a007-4f85-9d8b-ae20f0a79340"],
 " and verify the Weyl relation:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f50c0d77-3f6c-4bea-83e2-74bdb025815e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"d", " ", "=", " ", "3"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Omega]", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Exp", "[", 
    RowBox[{"2", " ", "Pi", " ", 
     RowBox[{"I", "/", "d"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"X", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"SparseArray", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"Mod", "[", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"n", " ", "+", " ", "1"}], ",", " ", "d"}], "]"}], " ", "+",
            " ", "1"}], ",", " ", 
          RowBox[{"n", " ", "+", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}], " ", "->", " ", "1"}], ",",
        " ", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"n", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", 
         RowBox[{"d", " ", "-", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"d", ",", " ", "d"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Z", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"DiagonalMatrix", "[", 
    RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "^", "n"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"n", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{"d", " ", "-", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Z", " ", ".", " ", "X"}], " ", "==", " ", 
   RowBox[{"\[Omega]", " ", 
    RowBox[{"X", " ", ".", " ", "Z"}]}]}], "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[2]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"749ea7a6-1f38-4d02-961e-9a88b142ddc9"],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[2]= ",ExpressionUUID->"bde41dc4-aab5-44ec-adda-e1a696e90244"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The result is ",
 Cell[BoxData["True"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3037c4c3-ed1a-4bba-ba16-ce5fcbf053fa"],
 ": this one identity is the discrete shadow of the Weyl (exponentiated) form \
of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["q", "TI"], "^"], ",", 
    OverscriptBox[
     StyleBox["p", "TI"], "^"]}], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   StyleBox["i", "TI"], "\[HBar]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a7feb0cc-9e3f-45d3-9894-556729b108a4"],
 ", since a finite group has no unbounded commutator to carry the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["i", "TI"], "\[HBar]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8be4fd3c-aa75-4097-97ad-3631902fa9f4"],
 " directly."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3fa08476-8a8a-4553-9691-503cafca6533"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A point of the phase-space grid is labelled by a pair ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["b", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1ac9328f-c7bf-4452-b54c-3c44fe301ce5"],
 " of integers mod ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["d", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "eb4d9447-6c20-437b-b57e-209503b2dfd1"],
 ", and the ",
 StyleBox["displacement operator",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " that translates to that point is a phase times a product of powers of \
shift and clock, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["D", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["b", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "\[Proportional]", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["b", "TI"]], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["a", "TI"]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "19e8d30b-cd68-4b68-a4cf-ba2e7539ae18"],
 ". These are the finite translations of phase space; applied to a state they \
move it rigidly around the grid."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"46afd79f-e476-4a33-b751-07178d24028e"],

Cell["\<\
Define the displacement operators and confirm they are unitary:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"14de9b35-1161-41a1-b5b5-cc3f9447e9e5"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"disp", "[", 
    RowBox[{"a_", ",", " ", "b_"}], "]"}], " ", ":=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"-", 
       RowBox[{"Exp", "[", 
        RowBox[{"I", " ", 
         RowBox[{"Pi", "/", "d"}]}], "]"}]}], ")"}], "^", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"a", " ", "b"}], ")"}]}], " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"MatrixPower", "[", 
      RowBox[{"X", ",", " ", "b"}], "]"}], " ", ".", " ", 
     RowBox[{"MatrixPower", "[", 
      RowBox[{"Z", ",", " ", "a"}], "]"}]}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Chop", " ", "@", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"UnitaryMatrixQ", "[", 
       RowBox[{"disp", "[", 
        RowBox[{"a", ",", " ", "b"}], "]"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"a", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{"d", " ", "-", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"b", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{"d", " ", "-", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], " ", "//", " ",
    "Flatten"}], " ", "//", " ", "Union"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[3]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"d3d7632b-1114-4d5f-bfdd-dc503e3d2aef"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", "True", "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[3]= ",ExpressionUUID->"16e0efb2-ecab-424f-8ecb-e301c4a5e92d"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Every entry is ",
 Cell[BoxData["True"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2b502823-96d6-453a-aab6-bd8998317918"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"25380ae3-3664-4d9b-96ed-b5efb2f49c1f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "What earns these ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["d", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3b402fe1-9449-4080-9a8b-84d37c0b7e0a"],
 " operators the name ",
 StyleBox["group", "TI"],
 " is closure: the product of any two displacements is again a displacement, \
up to a phase, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["D", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["a", "TI"], ",", 
      StyleBox["b", "TI"]}], 
     StyleBox[")",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}], " ", 
    StyleBox["D", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Prime]"], ",", 
      SuperscriptBox[
       StyleBox["b", "TI"], "\[Prime]"]}], 
     StyleBox[")",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}]}], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     StyleBox["phase",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], 
     StyleBox[")",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}], " ", 
    StyleBox["D", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["a", "TI"], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox[
        StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Prime]"]}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["b", "TI"], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox[
        StyleBox["b", "TI"], "\[Prime]"]}]}], 
     StyleBox[")",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "02e8785d-53d2-49d1-89fb-d1f7c220b207"],
 " with the labels added mod ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["d", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "974fe061-1174-4680-880c-7c6570842276"],
 ". Verify that composition law for every pair, and that the leftover phase \
always has modulus ",
 Cell[BoxData["1"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ee760733-db72-4d20-9fb9-7c875582bcf7"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"92817998-1ab7-4e57-ad91-5657491567d6"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"closureQ", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"a1_", ",", " ", "b1_"}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"a2_", ",", " ", "b2_"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], " ", ":=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"With", "[", "\n", "   ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"m", " ", "=", " ", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"disp", "[", 
         RowBox[{"a1", ",", " ", "b1"}], "]"}], " ", ".", " ", 
        RowBox[{"disp", "[", 
         RowBox[{"a2", ",", " ", "b2"}], "]"}], " ", ".", " ", 
        RowBox[{"ConjugateTranspose", "[", 
         RowBox[{"disp", "[", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"Mod", "[", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"a1", " ", "+", " ", "a2"}], ",", " ", "d"}], "]"}], ",",
            " ", 
           RowBox[{"Mod", "[", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"b1", " ", "+", " ", "b2"}], ",", " ", "d"}], "]"}]}], 
          "]"}], "]"}]}]}], "}"}], ",", "\n", "   ", 
     RowBox[{"With", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"ph", " ", "=", " ", 
         RowBox[{"m", "[", 
          RowBox[{"[", 
           RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"m", " ", "==", " ", 
          RowBox[{"ph", " ", 
           RowBox[{"IdentityMatrix", "[", "d", "]"}]}]}], " ", "&&", " ", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"Abs", "[", "ph", "]"}], " ", "==", " ", "1"}]}], "]"}]}], 
      "]"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"AllTrue", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Tuples", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Tuples", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Range", "[", 
        RowBox[{"0", ",", " ", 
         RowBox[{"d", " ", "-", " ", "1"}]}], "]"}], ",", " ", "2"}], "]"}], ",",
      " ", "2"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Apply", "[", "closureQ", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[4]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"503ffdf8-ed48-4bfc-b13c-ed0a291daa20"],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[4]= ",ExpressionUUID->"dd0ab435-eaac-45e4-a875-4909f6f7771e"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The result is ",
 Cell[BoxData["True"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3bfcd77a-8f80-48e3-bd40-3273ac9cb4ad"],
 ": every product of two displacements collapses to a single displacement \
times a unit-modulus phase (we divide the product by the expected ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["D", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["a", "TI"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["a", "TI"], "\[Prime]"]}], ",", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["b", "TI"], "+", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["b", "TI"], "\[Prime]"]}]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "05aa31f7-0a25-4a40-ada1-489a3bfc5ee2"],
 " and check the quotient is a phase times the identity). That closure, \
together with the identity ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["D", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{"0", ",", "0"}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "464c1021-7f5d-40ed-83c1-37648f99ee9a"],
 " and the inverses ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["D", "TI"], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["a", "TI"], ",", 
      StyleBox["b", "TI"]}], 
     StyleBox[")",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}], "\[Dagger]"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5fd185ce-f750-4c07-8efb-5ca4ced0df40"],
 ", is exactly the Heisenberg-Weyl group structure; the leftover phases form \
the group's center. The ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["d", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "0da3756c-131c-41de-895e-e024fa6566a2"],
 " displacements are the group we will expand everything in."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"038400ff-6a70-4ba0-b5a2-55774f93904d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The phase ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Tau]", "TI"], "=", "-", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["i", "TI"], "\[Pi]", "/", 
     StyleBox["d", "TI"]}]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a2eb5918-520d-47e4-aad1-060678ee6dcb"],
 " is Gross's odd-",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["d", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7b4a7c3d-aa81-4e69-b68c-ce1e1eb9b5f7"],
 " convention: a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["d", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e83f514b-7768-48af-bbba-21186b8d7227"],
 "-th root of unity (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Tau]", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["d", "TI"]], "=", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f5c904e2-d3b5-4fb8-a860-c0f59c1352ed"],
 ") that makes each ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["D", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["b", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "e11ba5c5-c5f9-437d-b8c2-8ce4ce14ee3d"],
 " have order ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["d", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c298b315-52d1-45d1-8a6e-c63899986100"],
 " and, below, the phase-point operators Hermitian. It is exactly this phase \
that has no clean counterpart for even ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["d", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3927ccf7-c755-4e00-9dc5-9f1088b4d52c"],
 ", the deeper reason a covariant qubit Wigner function does not exist. \
(QuantumFramework stores the conjugate clock ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"], "\[Function]", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["Z", "TI"], "\[Dagger]"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a258550e-b7fb-45ad-b2d8-d044733a1f5a"],
 " internally, an ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Omega]", "TI"], "\[LeftRightArrow]", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Omega]", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4c8ca18a-52db-40a3-827a-fc8156ba819b"],
 " relabeling that leaves the phase-point operators and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["W", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3171c6da-84d5-4586-8746-f39385f8a4c3"],
 " unchanged, which is why the hand-built and packaged Wigner values agree \
throughout.)"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"dda10465-2ce4-4293-a9ca-2c28102bcc7c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We built the clock, shift, and displacements by hand to see the structure \
in the open, but QuantumFramework already carries them as named operators, \
and from here on we let it. The generalized Pauli operators are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<X\>\"", "[", "d", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "864cda43-50d6-4c3e-89ec-920b401af50e"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Z\>\"", "[", "d", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "57c4e25f-5200-4880-a389-233b3da0be84"],
 ". Confirm that the framework's shift is the very matrix we built, and watch \
it translate a basis state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{"0"},
    "Ket"], "\[Rule]", 
   TemplateBox[{"1"},
    "Ket"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5fd2219a-28b5-4c75-95b3-78d0377ee391"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1220d532-c76d-4c67-b267-bc3e2ec69b6e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Normal", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<X\>\"", "[", "3", "]"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", 
      "]"}], "]"}], " ", "===", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Normal", "[", "X", "]"}]}], ",", "\n", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Normal", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<X\>\"", "[", "3", "]"}], "]"}], "[", 
      RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}], ",", " ", "3"}], 
       "]"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", "]"}], "]"}]}], 
  "}"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[5]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"d37fb17c-51a9-41aa-9259-4b8d89cd7098"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"True", ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0", ",", "1", ",", "0"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[5]= ",ExpressionUUID->"b70a8c84-0062-4dbc-b771-4ba30731d39c"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The pair is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"True", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"0", ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "58c492f8-de1e-4757-814a-e9926c00385f"],
 ": the framework's ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\"\<X\>\"", "[", "3", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "40f1831c-26aa-481d-9657-0056b8cfa6ac"],
 " is our shift matrix exactly, and applied to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c8461883-5b3e-482f-912f-f9a88d3753ca"],
 " it returns ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"1"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c59035c5-4288-4e89-a355-98bababeff0d"],
 ", the finite translation in action. The clock and the Weyl relation come \
along too, in the conjugate convention noted above. Check that the \
framework's operators satisfy ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Omega]", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}]], 
   StyleBox["X", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["Z", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c740721e-7a31-467b-8cb8-33234c648f70"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3bc7c53d-f08f-40d3-a2c2-be0882155113"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"qX", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<X\>\"", "[", "3", "]"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", 
    "]"}]}], ";", " ", 
  RowBox[{"qZ", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<Z\>\"", "[", "3", "]"}], "]"}], "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", 
    "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"qZ", " ", ".", " ", "qX"}], " ", "==", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Omega]", "^", 
     RowBox[{"-", "1"}]}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"qX", " ", ".", " ", "qZ"}]}]}], "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[6]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"1f3b3cfb-b360-45c2-aad5-c2d91d98467d"],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[6]= ",ExpressionUUID->"eb33756e-604a-4319-9fad-ea24dd334b8e"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData["True"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "09348ea7-e63b-4a22-9b65-5b62776b437d"],
 ": the framework's ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\"\<Z\>\"", "[", "3", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "51321461-1256-4eb2-a156-4ea56c72cba6"],
 " is the clock with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[Omega]", "TI"], "\[Rule]", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["\[Omega]", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}]]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "6212e642-4b9c-4d69-aa14-f3cfa0cc76c0"],
 ", so its Weyl relation is the mirror of the one we checked by hand. Same \
group, same physics, one relabeling of the phase. With these operators in \
hand, native or hand-built, we can assemble the phase-point operators and the \
Wigner function."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a322c149-354e-4ba5-8941-a215f009a440"],

Cell["2. Phase-point operators and the discrete Wigner function", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"2ee962cf-e284-406d-888c-629cc7f38dc9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In continuous phase space the Wigner function is the expectation of a \
displaced parity operator. The finite-dimensional construction, due to \
Wootters and sharpened by Gross for odd prime dimension, mirrors it exactly: \
to each grid point ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d817aae4-ace7-4d37-b768-69adebd49342"],
 " one assigns a ",
 StyleBox["phase-point operator",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "2f6eca1f-4dcc-49f7-a488-8332e97f9501"],
 ", a Hermitian unitary built from a displaced discrete parity, and the \
Wigner function of a state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a024d239-4970-4054-bcaa-80f7794e8335"],
 " is"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"06173499-a73d-48f0-a924-022580eddd7e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 PaneBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["W", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"]], 
    StyleBox["(",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
     StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
    StyleBox[")",
     SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
    FractionBox["1", 
     StyleBox["d", "TI"]], " ", 
    StyleBox["Tr",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[NegativeThinSpace]", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"], " ", 
     StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
     StyleBox["(",
      SpanMaxSize->1], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
      StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
     StyleBox[")",
      SpanMaxSize->1]}], "]"}], "."}],
  Alignment->Center,
  ImageSize->Full]], "DisplayFormula",ExpressionUUID->"27593f7c-ad6b-457d-\
8a58-1fa1a64683d7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["d", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3196e79a-f973-4055-ae9f-21675d2010f7"],
 " operators ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7490e2c5-63d3-4231-97b0-ae41bacdfdbe"],
 " form an orthogonal Hermitian basis of operator space, so this is an \
invertible change of description, not a lossy projection."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5e397665-20d9-4542-ba87-0b8c1d67ccd5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Concretely, the parity operator is the mean of all ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["d", "TI"], "2"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c17ffb44-49bc-4fa6-96a5-a87e5962512d"],
 " displacements, and the phase-point operator at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "ca8c8b00-2810-4649-bb53-3dfcbefc450a"],
 " is that parity displaced there:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fd128c1e-4853-45d7-a0f0-6c07bc649093"],

Cell[BoxData[
 PaneBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\\", "Pi"}], "=", 
    FractionBox["1", 
     StyleBox["d", "TI"]], 
    UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["a", "TI"], ",", 
      StyleBox["b", "TI"]}],
     LimitsPositioning->False], 
    StyleBox["D", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["(",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["a", "TI"], ",", 
     StyleBox["b", "TI"]}], 
    StyleBox[")",
     SpanMaxSize->1]}], ",", 
   "\[NonBreakingSpace]\[NonBreakingSpace]\[NonBreakingSpace]\
\[NonBreakingSpace]", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["(",
       SpanMaxSize->1], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
       StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
      StyleBox[")",
       SpanMaxSize->1]}]}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["D", "TI"], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["(",
       SpanMaxSize->1], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
       StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
      StyleBox[")",
       SpanMaxSize->1]}], " ", 
     RowBox[{"\\", "Pi"}], " ", 
     StyleBox["D", "TI"], 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["(",
        SpanMaxSize->1], 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
        StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
       StyleBox[")",
        SpanMaxSize->1]}], "\[Dagger]"]}]}], ",", 
   "\[NonBreakingSpace]\[NonBreakingSpace]\[NonBreakingSpace]\
\[NonBreakingSpace]", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["W", "TI"], 
      StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"]], 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["(",
       SpanMaxSize->1], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
       StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
      StyleBox[")",
       SpanMaxSize->1]}]}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox["1", 
      StyleBox["d", "TI"]], " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["Tr",
        FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[NegativeThinSpace]", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"], " ", 
        StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
        StyleBox["(",
         SpanMaxSize->1], 
        RowBox[{
         StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
         StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
        StyleBox[")",
         SpanMaxSize->1]}], "]"}], "."}]}]}]}],
  Alignment->Center,
  ImageSize->Full]], "DisplayFormula",ExpressionUUID->"fdf72aae-91c9-428c-\
903e-d76b345821e3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Build ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\\", "Pi"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "09bb9471-c582-45f5-86d6-a1e77fcd4961"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["A", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "df24c55c-1f9a-4ead-ad4d-c02f9972eaac"],
 " from the displacements of Section 1, and confirm ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\\", "Pi"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "90db518a-1d2f-4379-9ddc-9fb5749007a7"],
 " is a genuine parity, Hermitian and squaring to the identity (it reflects \
the grid about the origin):"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8bb5cc47-86f5-4d01-a300-2084aa7bd1ea"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[CapitalPi]", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"1", "/", "d"}], ")"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"Sum", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"disp", "[", 
       RowBox[{"a", ",", " ", "b"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"a", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{"d", " ", "-", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"b", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{"d", " ", "-", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}]}], 
  ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"A", "[", 
    RowBox[{"q_", ",", " ", "p_"}], "]"}], " ", ":=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"disp", "[", 
     RowBox[{"q", ",", " ", "p"}], "]"}], " ", ".", " ", "\[CapitalPi]", " ", 
    ".", " ", 
    RowBox[{"ConjugateTranspose", "[", 
     RowBox[{"disp", "[", 
      RowBox[{"q", ",", " ", "p"}], "]"}], "]"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\[CapitalPi]", " ", "==", " ", 
     RowBox[{"ConjugateTranspose", "[", "\[CapitalPi]", "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
   " ", 
   RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[CapitalPi]", " ", ".", " ", "\[CapitalPi]"}], " ", "==", " ", 
     
     RowBox[{"IdentityMatrix", "[", "d", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[7]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"f9812bc9-d856-4257-8d38-c80a1f48b698"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"True", ",", "True"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[7]= ",ExpressionUUID->"64645859-7945-491a-af10-100b1067e252"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Both ",
 Cell[BoxData["True"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "5a7dd258-cacf-4c26-b87f-39118741e31f"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\\", "Pi"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "302a79b7-5448-4afb-b8b5-29166542e5b7"],
 " is the discrete parity, and each ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "aa3e3aa2-fae4-4064-9432-4c736a642c99"],
 " is its translate to the grid point ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "816ab38a-d1e5-417a-9b67-833fed63f01b"],
 ", the Hermitian unitary the formula promised."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9379247e-c4f1-4fee-a006-9e52c27418ab"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "QuantumFramework packages the whole construction. The transform sends a \
state into the phase-space picture, and the ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<QuasiProbability\>\""], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "972fb4a0-2686-4e24-8da0-2d1620fea96f"],
 " property returns the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["d", "TI"], "\[Times]", 
   StyleBox["d", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "4ba5e479-c3e0-4b4c-b16f-4ae8852cd753"],
 " table ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["W", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "8ab040e1-82cc-4bb6-96f0-81ee4f654cfd"],
 ". Compute the discrete Wigner function of the computational state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"0"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "9553cf81-874b-4143-b9d8-7317c515da82"],
 " in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["d", "TI"], "=", "3"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "eda60b9a-8bdc-409a-827a-0f591515830a"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c42eda3e-404e-404a-b2e5-12a78e7f4ddb"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Psi]0", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "0"}], "}"}], ",", " ", "3"}], 
    "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"w0", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"\[Psi]0", "[", "\"\<QuasiProbability\>\"", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"MatrixForm", " ", "@", " ", 
  RowBox[{"Chop", " ", "@", " ", "w0"}]}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[8]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"a58f5948-cb81-4df7-896e-747c7a2e5141"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      FractionBox["1", "3"], "0", "0"},
     {
      FractionBox["1", "3"], "0", "0"},
     {
      FractionBox["1", "3"], "0", "0"}
    },
    GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
    GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
         Offset[0.7]}, 
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
        Offset[0.2], {
         Offset[0.4]}, 
        Offset[0.2]}}], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}],
  Function[BoxForm`e$, 
   MatrixForm[
   SparseArray[
    Automatic, {3, 3}, 0, {
     1, {{0, 1, 2, 3}, {{1}, {1}, {1}}}, {
      Rational[1, 3], Rational[1, 3], Rational[1, 3]}}]]]]], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[8]= ",ExpressionUUID->"d8eb348a-e53d-41ef-97d6-3028f54a9351"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The output is a real ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"3", "\[Times]", "3"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "a7c215ac-ca49-43f4-b057-fda874d1f7af"],
 " table. Two defining properties make it a genuine phase-space distribution. \
First it is normalized, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
     StyleBox["p", "TI"]}],
    LimitsPositioning->False], 
   StyleBox["W", "TI"], "=", "1"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "7b7820ba-dfd9-44c4-a16d-e85276840f92"],
 ". Second its marginals are the measurement probabilities: summing ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["W", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "3a6c0409-65f9-4656-a49a-b26370d85653"],
 " along one axis returns the outcome distribution in the corresponding basis."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e7722398-a520-4786-aa43-ef9082a1ef05"],

Cell["\<\
Verify normalization and that the position marginal reproduces the Born \
probabilities:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e6853715-eb9d-40a0-afbd-76cce9279a49"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Total", "[", 
     RowBox[{"w0", ",", " ", "2"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Chop", " ", "@", " ", 
     RowBox[{"Total", "[", "w0", "]"}]}]}], "}"}], " ", "==", " ", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"\[Psi]0", "[", "\"\<ProbabilitiesList\>\"", "]"}]}], 
   "}"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[9]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"a20aee5f-9e29-4d45-9c09-bb2d7efe62c7"],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[9]= ",ExpressionUUID->"099dad46-8748-4865-8eb7-629616308ee2"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData["True"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "d4658280-73bd-4302-b684-4bf53dfd9f54"],
 ". The Wigner function carries the same information as the state, arranged \
on the grid so that measurements are marginals, exactly as in the continuous \
theory."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a1ec9a9d-375b-4c82-bc99-1bc16e710b06"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The packaged ",
 Cell[BoxData["\"\<QuasiProbability\>\""], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "712f54c4-9d25-4b36-a503-33339968b759"],
 " is nothing other than our trace formula. Evaluate ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    StyleBox["d", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox["Tr",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"], " ", 
    StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["(",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
     StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
    StyleBox[")",
     SpanMaxSize->1]}], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "79d8b96e-4a8f-473e-b2fa-904bca53ddd1"],
 " by hand on the phase-point operators we built, and compare:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a592488c-0263-4746-ba6b-015fd1da3ffb"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Whand", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"1", "/", "d"}], ")"}], " ", 
      RowBox[{"Tr", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"\[Psi]0", "[", "\"\<DensityMatrix\>\"", "]"}], " ", ".", " ", 
        RowBox[{"A", "[", 
         RowBox[{"q", ",", " ", "p"}], "]"}]}], "]"}]}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"q", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"d", " ", "-", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"p", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", 
       RowBox[{"d", " ", "-", " ", "1"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Simplify", "[", 
  RowBox[{"Whand", " ", "==", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Normal", "[", "w0", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[10]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"6497feae-e26d-4c5b-bcef-18192dacadf5"],

Cell[BoxData["True"], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[10]= ",ExpressionUUID->"b8ef5a37-7095-4812-ad74-0e3a815a77d7"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData["True"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "499b6e0d-e104-4a03-ac29-a3aca4d9ed75"],
 ": the framework computes exactly ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["W", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox["(",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
    StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    SpanMaxSize->1], "=", 
   FractionBox["1", 
    StyleBox["d", "TI"]], 
   StyleBox["Tr",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   StyleBox["[",
    SpanMaxSize->1], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[Rho]", "TI"], " ", 
    StyleBox["A", "TI"], 
    StyleBox["(",
     SpanMaxSize->1], 
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["q", "TI"], ",", 
     StyleBox["p", "TI"]}], 
    StyleBox[")",
     SpanMaxSize->1]}], 
   StyleBox["]",
    SpanMaxSize->1]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "126da9f3-116b-4d41-8cb2-9c9f80f8897f"],
 " on the Gross phase-point operators. From here we let it, and read the \
physics off the table."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"99b6b780-b94b-4143-a074-a91204239184"],

Cell["3. Negativity and the discrete Hudson theorem", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"b1c45584-a2d6-485f-9220-673cbdc160d0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Here the finite theory earns its keep. A classical probability distribution \
on phase space is nonnegative; a Wigner function need not be. For continuous \
systems Hudson's theorem says the only pure states with a nonnegative Wigner \
function are Gaussians. Gross proved the finite-dimensional analogue for odd \
dimension: ",
 StyleBox["the pure states with a nonnegative discrete Wigner function are \
exactly the stabilizer states.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Negativity is therefore a sharp, computable signature of non-stabilizer \
resources, the states that a Clifford computer cannot reach."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"940a5eb9-bde5-427c-b0f9-e850020703af"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Compare a stabilizer state to a non-stabilizer one. The state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{"+"},
   "Ket"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "1be7d7a6-0c65-4bda-b5bf-ad7aa1712a85"],
 " (the equal superposition, a stabilizer state in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["d", "TI"], "=", "3"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "b77e02c2-8144-4e6c-a7b4-3d03140dd89f"],
 ") should be nonnegative; the \"strange state\" ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{
     StyleBox["S", "TI"]},
    "Ket"], "\[Proportional]", 
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"1"},
     "Ket"], "-", 
    TemplateBox[{"2"},
     "Ket"]}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "461fb701-a560-4d38-9211-bcba6f4ea870"],
 ", a standard magic state for the qutrit, should go negative."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"50921c7a-e91a-429c-af37-aed9c276d1ce"],

Cell["Compute the minimum Wigner value for each:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e3f4a4c0-d9f3-4866-a374-245e7a33c6d4"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"plus", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}], "/", 
      RowBox[{"Sqrt", "[", "3", "]"}]}], ",", " ", "3"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"strange", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"0", ",", " ", "1", ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{"-", "1"}]}], "}"}], "/", 
      RowBox[{"Sqrt", "[", "2", "]"}]}], ",", " ", "3"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Min", " ", "@", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Chop", " ", "@", " ", 
     RowBox[{"plus", "[", "\"\<QuasiProbability\>\"", "]"}]}]}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Min", " ", "@", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Chop", " ", "@", " ", 
     RowBox[{"strange", "[", "\"\<QuasiProbability\>\"", "]"}]}]}]}], 
  "}"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[11]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"6aef10d7-7182-4e6c-8138-da5d1c456534"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0", ",", 
   RowBox[{"-", 
    FractionBox["1", "3"]}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[11]= ",ExpressionUUID->"69e7d488-553b-4911-908e-d0be9a332af3"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The first minimum is ",
 Cell[BoxData["0"], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "f1aefcd7-e3d5-4f09-9ef8-e83ba951f215"],
 " (the stabilizer state stays nonnegative) and the second is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"-", "1", "/", "3"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontSize->0.9 Inherited,ExpressionUUID->
  "c439d0bf-f6b9-4b8d-9f70-9ecb43feba3f"],
 " (the magic state dips below zero). Negativity is present precisely when \
the state is outside the stabilizer polytope."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"34c7f45a-87bf-45ed-a334-4a9d4dbc0428"],

Cell["\<\
Seeing it helps. Plot the strange state's Wigner table as a heat map over the \
phase-space grid, diverging from white at zero, blue below, red above, with a \
legend for the value:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"aa00454e-d423-40a6-b3dc-06be660c727b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"With", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"w", " ", "=", " ", 
      RowBox[{"N", " ", "@", " ", 
       RowBox[{"strange", "[", "\"\<QuasiProbability\>\"", "]"}]}]}], ",", 
     " ", 
     RowBox[{"m", " ", "=", " ", 
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "3."}]}]}], "}"}], ",", "\n", " ", 
   RowBox[{"ArrayPlot", "[", 
    RowBox[{"w", ",", "\n", "  ", 
     RowBox[{"ColorFunction", " ", "->", " ", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"ColorData", "[", "\"\<TemperatureMap\>\"", "]"}], "[", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{"#", " ", "+", " ", "m"}], ")"}], "/", 
          RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{"2", " ", "m"}], ")"}]}], "]"}], " ", "&"}], ")"}]}], ",", 
     " ", 
     RowBox[{"ColorFunctionScaling", " ", "->", " ", "False"}], ",", "\n", 
     "  ", 
     RowBox[{"Mesh", " ", "->", " ", "True"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"FrameTicks", " ", "->", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "\"\<0\>\""}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{"2", ",", " ", "\"\<1\>\""}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{"3", ",", " ", "\"\<2\>\""}], "}"}]}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{"1", ",", " ", "\"\<0\>\""}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{"2", ",", " ", "\"\<1\>\""}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{"3", ",", " ", "\"\<2\>\""}], "}"}]}], "}"}]}], "}"}]}], ",",
      "\n", "  ", 
     RowBox[{"FrameLabel", " ", "->", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<position q\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<momentum p\>\""}], 
       "}"}]}], ",", "\n", "  ", 
     RowBox[{
     "PlotLabel", " ", "->", 
      " ", "\"\<Discrete Wigner function W(q,p): strange state\>\""}], ",", 
     "\n", "  ", 
     RowBox[{"PlotLegends", " ", "->", " ", 
      RowBox[{"BarLegend", "[", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"ColorData", "[", "\"\<TemperatureMap\>\"", "]"}], "[", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"(", 
              RowBox[{"#", " ", "+", " ", "m"}], ")"}], "/", 
             RowBox[{"(", 
              RowBox[{"2", " ", "m"}], ")"}]}], "]"}], " ", "&"}], ")"}], ",",
          " ", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"-", "m"}], ",", " ", "m"}], "}"}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}]}], 
    "]"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[12]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"70799bf4-76bd-4e34-960e-462d83ff68e9"],

